  "summary": "claudechor exfiltrates host credentials and identity to attacker-controlled endpoint",
  "details": "index.js reads files from the user's home directory (os.homedir()), collects host identity via os.hostname() and os.userInfo(), and POSTs the collected data to a hardcoded attacker-controlled endpoint at https://tfer.jha-anurag2017.workers.dev using https.request. The script combines filesystem reads, base64 encoding (Buffer.from(..., 'base64')), and outbound HTTPS to a Cloudflare Workers domain that bears no relation to any documented package purpose. This is a credential/data exfiltration payload typical of supply-chain attack packages.",
